wdi-DT.DOD.DSTC.ZS.def: Short-term debt includes all debt having an original maturity of one year or less and interest in arrears on long-term debt. Total external debt is debt owed to nonresidents repayable in currency, goods, or services. Total external debt is the sum of public, publicly guaranteed, and private nonguaranteed long-term debt, use of IMF credit, and short-term debt.
wdi-DT.DOD.DSTC.ZS.name: Short-term debt
